---
title: HTML Batch Validator
description: Batch validate multiple pages on your website from a sitemap file using the official W3C Markup Validator API. Supports HTML5, XHTML, HTML3-4 and SGML.
date: 2020-06-15
---

p This tool validates a range of <abbr title="Uniform Resource Identifiers">URI</abbr>'s against the official <a href="https://validator.w3.org/docs/api.html">W3C Markup Validation Web Service</a>. Simply enter the URI of your sitemap file, and this tool will automatically read and validate the linked pages from the file. The sitemap must be in the <a href="https://www.sitemaps.org/protocol.html">Sitemap</a> or <abbr title="Really Simple Syndication">RSS</abbr> feed format.

p In accordance with best practices for consuming remote resources, this tool will only process <i>one URI per second</i> so not to overload the validator web service.

form#validator.c
  label
    b Sitemap URI:
    br
    input#sitemapuri.text(
      autofocus='autofocus'
      placeholder='https://my.domain/sitemap.xml'
      required
      style='width:500px'
      tabindex='0'
      type='url'
  )
  | &nbsp;
  input.button(type='submit', value='Validate')


h3 Validation results

table.table(style='width:100%')
  colgroup
    col(style='width:40px')
    col
    col(style='width:80px')
  thead
    tr
      th.r #
      th URI
      th.c Result
  tbody#results
    tr
      td.c(colspan='3')
        i Click "Validate" to process the sitemap

script(src="/scripts/validator.js")
